# Spec Completeness Checker

You are checking a finished implementation against a written spec — not building anything, not fixing anything yet. Your only job is to produce an honest pass/fail report.

## Instructions

1. Read `/docs/specs/campaign-canvas-v1-spec.md` in full — do not rely on any memory of prior conversation about this project.
2. Read the actual current state of the code under `src/features/campaign-canvas/` (or the equivalent path) — components, not just file names.
3. Go through **every single checkbox in Section 5 (Acceptance Criteria)** of the spec, one at a time. For each item:
   - Mark **PASS** only if you can point to the specific file/component/line that implements it
   - Mark **FAIL** if it's missing, partially implemented, or you're not certain
   - Mark **UNVERIFIABLE** if it requires actually running the app to confirm (e.g. "no console errors on zoom") — list these separately for the human to check manually
4. Also check Section 0 (boundaries) — flag any violation (backend code, Unibox logic, Workflow Engine coupling, disallowed features like undo/redo) even though these aren't in the Section 5 checklist.
5. Also check Section 2.10 — confirm custom `nodeTypes`/`edgeTypes` are actually registered and used, not just default React Flow nodes with CSS.

## Output format

Produce a table: `Item | Status | Evidence/Location | Notes`

End with:
- Total pass / fail / unverifiable count
- A prioritized list of what to fix first (broken interactions before cosmetic gaps)
- Explicit confirmation: "No Section 0 boundary violations found" OR a list of violations

## What NOT to do

- Do not fix anything yourself in this pass — this is a report, not a repair
- Do not soften a FAIL into a "mostly there" — the spec is a checklist, not a vibe check
- Do not assume something works because it looks like it should — verify against actual code
